#loading mta data from jun to may in 2019
def get_data(week_nums):
    url = "http://web.mta.info/developers/data/nyct/turnstile/turnstile_{}.txt"
    dfs = []
    for week_num in week_nums:
        file_url = url.format(week_num)
        dfs.append(pd.read_csv(file_url))
    return pd.concat(dfs)
        
week_nums = [190105,190112,190119,190126,190202,190209,190216,190223,190302, 190309, 190316,190323,190330,190406, 190413, 190420,190427,190504,190511,190518,190525]
turnstiles_df_4 = get_data(week_nums)

In [118]:
def get_daily_entry_counts(row, max_counter):
    counter = row["ENTRIES"] - row["PREV_ENTRIES"]
    
    if counter < 0:
        counter = -counter  # adjust for "reverse" counter
        
    if counter > max_counter:
        # Maybe counter was reset, so it may make sense to take the minimum
        print(f'entries: {row["ENTRIES"]} <-- {row["PREV_ENTRIES"]}')
        counter = min(row["ENTRIES"], row["PREV_ENTRIES"])
        
    if counter > max_counter:
        # If we still get a counter that is too big, set to zero
        return 0
    
    return counter
In [119]:
turnstiles_df_4_daily_entry["DAILY_ENTRIES"] = turnstiles_df_4_daily_entry.apply(get_daily_entry_counts, axis=1, max_counter=86400)

In [120]:
def get_daily_exit_counts(row, max_counter):
    counter = row["EXITS"] - row["PREV_EXITS"]
    
    if counter < 0:
        counter = -counter  # adjust for "reverse" counter
        
    if counter > max_counter:
        # Maybe counter was reset, so it may make sense to take the minimum
        print(f'exits: {row["EXITS"]} <-- {row["PREV_EXITS"]}')
        counter = min(row["EXITS"], row["PREV_EXITS"])
        
    if counter > max_counter:
        # If we still get a counter that is too big, set to zero
        return 0
    
    return counter
In [121]:
turnstiles_df_4_daily_exit["DAILY_EXITS"] = turnstiles_df_4_daily_exit.apply(get_daily_exit_counts, axis=1, max_counter=86400)

#For each ControlArea/UNIT/STATION combo, for each day
ca_unit_station_daily_entry = turnstiles_df_4_daily_entry.groupby(["C/A", "UNIT", "SCP", "STATION", "LINENAME", "DIVISION", "DATE"])[['DAILY_ENTRIES']].sum().reset_index()
ca_unit_station_daily_exit = turnstiles_df_4_daily_exit.groupby(["C/A", "UNIT", "STATION", "LINENAME", "DIVISION", "DATE"])[['DAILY_EXITS']].sum().reset_index()
In [124]:
#daily time series for each STATION
station_daily_entry = turnstiles_df_4_daily_entry.groupby(["LINENAME", "DIVISION", "STATION", "DATE"])[['DAILY_ENTRIES']].sum().reset_index()
station_daily_exit = turnstiles_df_4_daily_exit.groupby(["LINENAME", "DIVISION", "STATION", "DATE"])[['DAILY_EXITS']].sum().reset_index()
In [125]:
station_daily = pd.merge(station_daily_entry, station_daily_exit, on = ["LINENAME", "DIVISION", "STATION", "DATE"])

# Count how many entries in the crime/complaint dataframe fall within each of the circular polygon buffer by station

def count_complaints(polygon):
    
    num = 0
    for _, complaint in crime_df_up_5.iterrows():
        p = Point(complaint["LONG"], complaint["LAT"])
        
        if polygon.contains(p):
            
         num += 1
         
    return num

)
